name: r-investr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.4.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-investr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/investr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/investr/investr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2a07537777b95370f574b597e1d97279cd700ec9d17d2bad8a1c8ef846dc198a

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-nlme
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-nlme

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('investr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('investr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/bgreenwell/investr
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Functions to facilitate inverse estimation (e.g., calibration) in linear, generalized linear, nonlinear, and (linear) mixed-effects models. A generic function is also provided for plotting fitted regression models with or without confidence/prediction bands that may be of use to the general user.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
